# Domain docs — automatic slice (no @ required)

## User does NOT pick files

Infer **one** domain from the task text (FR/EN). Hooks inject `[AUTO-DOMAIN: …]` when matched; otherwise use `docs/DOMAINS.md` + `docs/intent-map.json`.

Examples (no paths needed from user):

| User says | Open only |
|-----------|-----------|
| « refaire l’écran résultats » | `docs/domains/design.md` + UI code |
| « marge vs markup » | `docs/FORMULAS.md` |
| « cas 07 » | `docs/TEST_CASES.md` |
| « P0 stack » | `TODO.md` + `docs/domains/architecture.md` if stack |

If two domains seem needed → pick the **primary**; ask one short question only if blocked.

## Workflow

1. **Detect** — hook context or keyword match on `intent-map.json`
2. **Open** — that slice + related code (`code_roots` in map)
3. **Edit** — slice + code only
4. **Close** — do not re-read other domains; no pasteback of whole docs

## Hard limits

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| 1 domain doc + grep/code as needed | `PROJECT_BRIEF.md` body, multiple domains |
| Trust `[AUTO-DOMAIN: id]` prefix | Handoff unless `fin` or `@` |

Adding a new area (e.g. `api`): create `docs/domains/api.md` + row in `intent-map.json`.
